import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='values')
    mean_value = data['values'].mean()
    plt.axhline(mean_value, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {mean_value:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average value of volcano eruptions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    num_unique_values = data.nunique()
    sns.barplot(x=num_unique_values.index, y=num_unique_values.values)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of unique values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
